# AI Tool Approval and Onboarding Process

**{{ business_name }}**
*Effective Date: {{ effective_date }}*
*Version: {{ version }}*

---

## 1. Purpose

This document establishes the formal process for requesting, evaluating, approving, and onboarding new AI tools and services at {{ business_name }}. It ensures that all AI tool adoption decisions are assessed for privacy, security, and governance risks in accordance with the **Privacy Act 1988**, the **Australian Privacy Principles (APPs)**, the **AI6 Guidance for AI Adoption** (October 2024), and the **OAIC guidance on privacy and AI** (October 2024).

---

## 2. Scope

This process applies to:

- Any new AI-powered tool, platform, API, or plugin proposed for use at {{ business_name }}
- Free-tier, trial, or sandbox usage of AI tools that process organisational or personal data
- AI features embedded within existing software (e.g., Copilot, Gemini, AI assistants)
- Open-source AI models proposed for deployment on {{ business_name }}'s infrastructure
- AI tools used by third parties or contractors on behalf of {{ business_name }}

{% if shadow_ai_controls %}
{{ business_name }} has shadow AI controls in place. Any AI tool adoption that bypasses this process will be treated as a shadow AI incident and escalated under the AI Acceptable Use Policy.
{% else %}
**Warning:** {{ business_name }} does not currently have shadow AI controls in place. Implementing this approval process is a critical first step toward preventing unauthorised AI tool usage across the organisation.
{% endif %}

